pageContext.claim: “I was with the Prime Minister Abe of Japan. He's got many companies moving in, I said: ‘Look, we have a big deficit with you, we take care of your military and we have a deficit. What's going on?’ He said, ‘We are moving many companies into the United States.’ And he is.”
pageContext.analysis: The Japanese prime minister does not make decisions for the private companies operating in his country, so this purported conversation seems like a big stretch at best.
